		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">wiki wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">#  Cycles 256-319: Sprite fetches (8 sprites total, 8 cycles per sprite)<br /><br />    * 1-4: Read the Y-coordinate, tile number, attributes, and X-coordinate of the selected sprite<br />    * 5-8: Read the X-coordinate of the selected sprite 4 times.<br />    * On the first empty sprite slot, read the Y-coordinate of sprite #63 followed by $FF for the remaining 7 cycles<br />    * On all subsequent empty sprite slots, read $FF for all 8 reads</div>
<br />
<br />- Is this "read" a 2004h read OR the usual PPU "read-and-throw-away"?
<br />- Is this the MMC3 IRQ clocking period?

		

