		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It's different because the PPU takes over the OAM address, and doesn't need to use the CPU's interface. 
<br />
<br />What do you mean exactly by "read-and-throw-away"? If you mean it has no effect on the CPU, I guess that's right unless the program accesses $2004.
<br />
<br />The MMC3 could be affected I believe by at least cycles 5-8 when the PPU fetches sprite patterns (and "throws away" the OAM read value), I'm not sure how the address toggles between reads though.

		

